
Step 1. Install dependencies
 npm install

Step 2. Local development (if you see Internal Server Error, use dev:clean)
 npm run dev:clean

 Open the URL shown in terminal (often http://localhost:3000)

Step 3. Environment variables — copy .env.local.example to .env.local and set:
 - NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID (Google Analytics)
 - NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSPREE_ID (contact form)

Step 4. Deploy to Firebase (updates live site)
 npx firebase-tools login
 npm run deploy

Note: firebase.json uses "public": "out" for Next.js static export.
